The paper proposes a new class of parameter-sharing neural networks for relational databases, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields in computer science. Given the focus on deep learning and neural networks, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with databases and data modeling, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as another likely category. The use of knowledge graphs and the focus on relational data suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a third likely category. The paper also deals with optimization and complexity, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a fourth likely category. Finally, the paper deals with symmetry and equivariance, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a fifth likely category.
